html: I just read Pauline Hopkins' Of One Blood for a class. Written in 1903, it probably is the first speculative fiction novel by an African-American woman. Some ghostly encounters, mesmerism & a hidden city in Ethiopia. Not the best ever, but absolutely deserving of more notoriety.
